===

VOCABULARY SELECTION RULES
1. Quantity: Exactly 10-12 vocabulary words
2. Selection: Key words for understanding the article, appropriate for difficulty level
3. Word: In English
4. Meaning: In {{ nativeLanguage }}
5. Sentence: Exact sentence from the article
6. Phonetic: IPA transcription in {{ englishVariant }} style
   - DJ (British) if en-GB
   - KK (American) if en-US

===

OUTPUT FORMAT (JSON)
@raw
{
  "title": "Article title in English",
  "tableOfContents": ["Chapter 1: The Beginning", "Chapter 2: The Adventure", "Chapter 3: The Resolution"],
  "chapterCount": 3,
  "content": "Chapter 1: The Beginning\n\n[Content here...]\n\nChapter 2: The Adventure\n\n[Content here...]",
  "wordCount": 1234,
  "tags": [
    {"name": "科技", "isNew": false},
    {"name": "新标签", "isNew": true}
  ],
  "vocabulary": [
    {
      "word": "innovation",
      "meaning": "创新；革新",
      "sentence": "The company's innovation in technology changed the industry.",
      "phonetic": "/ˌɪnəˈveɪʃn/"
    }
  ]
}
@end

IMPORTANT:
- "tableOfContents" MUST be an array of chapter title strings
- "chapterCount" MUST be the number of chapters (length of tableOfContents array)
- Content MUST include chapter titles as section headers
- Set "isNew" to false for existing system tags, true for new tags
- Tags and vocabulary meanings MUST be in {{ nativeLanguage }}
- Vocabulary sentences MUST be exact quotes from the article
- Word count MUST be accurate (count all words in content)

Generate the article now following the structured process and quality requirements.